			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New.  Of course.<a name="75481"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 15 05 7:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>OK you've been playing for about a year.  This implies you should know enough about the game that general game mechanics are not in your way. But I won't make assumptions.
<br />

<br />
Tutorial: Did you do it with the bard?  If not, WAY too bad for you.    You could have gotten full burlap armor and an equivilent of fine steel sword by level 5.
<br />

<br />
Armor and Weapons: Whatcha got?  At level 11 you should be able to solo blues in patchwork/tattered or better and these are easily obtained.  Newbie bard armor would be better and the bazaar will have better still if you have the money (more later).  On weapons, you should be able to find something cheap and good enough for your needs in the bazaar.. go for speed over damage for gaining weapon skills.
<br />

<br />
Money: How are you situated?  If you are a non-twink and are strapped for cash, I suggest you spend some time killing goblins in Butcherblock.  At level 11, you can probably do 3 camps in the spawn time 1) North of the Wayfarers camp, 2) Down near Dagnors, south of crossroads and 3) North and a bit west of crossroads.  Cycle between these, goblin blood goes for over 4 plat.  You will run into some greenbloods, their insignias go for the same.  Kill any skunks you see.. their claws go for a plat plus.  A little time spent smacking down goblins and you will be able to afford some nice gear for the level, there are some sweet bargains in the bazaar
<br />

<br />
Now on to more bard-specific items.  I am going to address some very basic issues.  If they are too basic do not be offended, just covering possibilities here.
<br />

<br />
Twisting: Do you know what it is?  Are you twisting?  Are you having difficulty with it?  At level 11 you should be habitually 3-twisting.  By this I mean, Singing 3 songs that are all in effect at the same time, before the first wears off.  It should be pointed out here that a 4-twist is possible, but not the true measure of a bard.  Twisting 3 or more useful songs almost all the time IS the standard of a true bard.
<br />

<br />
It is possible that you don't know what I mean.  It is possible that you know ABOUT twisting, but don't do it.  If either of these is true, THAT is your problem. 
<br />

<br />
You start a song... the spell countdown begins... the countdown ends... the song takes effect... it lasts 3 &quot;ticks&quot; (6 second server clock intervals)... meanwhile you start and land another song.. then another song.. then back to the first again before the third &quot;tick&quot; of the first song expires... ad infinitum.  This is the power of the bard (that and moving while casting) 
<br />

<br />
Song choices and approach: For soloing at level 11, if you are meleeing while twisting; hymn (regen), jonathons (self haste/buff), and chords (AOE damage) against most single blue mobs, you probably have the mob WAY outclassed.  To avoid having chords (level 2) be a problem, pull your single mob to someplace the 2 of you can be alone (/wink).  To GET your single mob, thats what Lugubrious Lament is for.  Lull his friends on the pull.
<br />

<br />
Hope you get past your difficulties.  My guesses are its either underequipped (easily remedied) or bard specific mechanincs (twisting) or song selection that are your stumbling blocks.  Post back here and let us know what you conclude. 
<br />

<br />
Keep tunes in your heart and knives out of your back
<br />
Reys</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
